The rumen content can be removed in severe cases. This is preferably done using a tube, in a tedious process called rumen lavage.
Large amounts of water are pumped into the rumen and drained out by gravity. The process is repeated several times to dilute and drain out the lactic acid.
The rumen content can also be removed through surgery. However, in most cases, doctors avoid surgery because of its high cost and tendency for the animals to get abdominal infections. 
